31) What is the difference between Worker and Prefork MPM?\par
Answer : Both MPMs, Worker and prefork has their own mechanism to work with Apache. It totally depends on you that in which mode you want to start your Apache.\par
Basic difference between Worker and MPM(Multi Processing Modules) is in their process of spawning the child process. In the Prefork MPM, a master httpd process is started and this master process starts manages all other child processes to serve client requests. Whereas, In the worker MPM one httpd process is active, and it uses different threads to serve client requests.\par
Prefork MPM uses multiple child processes with one thread each, where worker MPM uses multiple child processes with many threads each.\par
Connection handling in the Prefork MPM, each process handles one connection at a time, whereas in the Worker mpm each thread handles one connection at a time.\par
Memory footprints Prefork MPM Large memory footprints, where Worker has smaller memory footprints.\par
